          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632824463677-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a medium sized pot with a lid over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once beginning to soften, add the <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>drained black beans</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and cook, covered, for 10 min or until the beans are very soft</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632824467874-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
